Note:
CSS Parser Test Suite

Tests: 6 test files
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/css/css_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/io/file.runa" as File

@Reasoning:
Counter triple shared across the CSS parser driver. Same layout as the
other language test suites so a future unified runner can consume any
of them without struct conversion.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total at offset 0, passed at 8, failed at 16; mutated via
Layout.memory_set_int64 because results is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Top-level driver for the CSS parser corpus. Exercises six stylesheets
that together cover the CSS surface area most prone to lexer/parser
regression: basic declarations, selector complexity, layout, color
notation, animations, and at-rules. Returning 1 on any failure makes
this binary CI-friendly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate TestResults, print header, call test_parse_file for each of
the six .css fixtures, print_results, then return 1 if results.failed
> 0 else 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All six stylesheets parse to AST with root node type 200 (CSS_STYLESHEET) -> exit 0
- Any stylesheet fails to read -> "Failed to read file", exit 1
- Parser returns null on a valid file -> "Parser returned null AST", exit 1
- AST root node type != 200 -> "Invalid root node type", exit 1
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_parse_file with "tests/translation/css/stylesheets/basic_styles.css", results
    proc test_parse_file with "tests/translation/css/stylesheets/selectors.css", results
    proc test_parse_file with "tests/translation/css/stylesheets/layout.css", results
    proc test_parse_file with "tests/translation/css/stylesheets/colors_units.css", results
    proc test_parse_file with "tests/translation/css/stylesheets/animations.css", results
    proc test_parse_file with "tests/translation/css/stylesheets/at_rules.css", results

    proc print_results from results

    If results.failed is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Per-file parse probe used by main. Pulled out so the counter mutation
and root-tag check live in exactly one place; the only thing that
varies between corpus files is the path argument.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. Increment results.total.
2. read_file(file_path); null -> "Failed to read file" failure.
3. parse_css(content); null -> free content, "Parser returned null AST".
4. Verify memory_get_int64(ast, 0) equals 200 (CSS_STYLESHEET tag);
   otherwise free content, "Invalid root node type".
5. On success print [PASS], free content, increment results.passed.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- stylesheets/basic_styles.css -> AST root tag 200, results.passed += 1
- Non-existent path -> read_file == 0 -> failure with "Failed to read file"
- Lexer regression on selectors.css -> ast == 0 -> "Parser returned null AST"
- Parser builds AST but tags wrong root -> "Invalid root node type"
@End TestCases

Process called "test_parse_file" takes file_path as Integer, results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let content be proc read_file from File with file_path

    If content is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with file_path, "Failed to read file"
        Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ast be proc parse_css from Parser with content

    If ast is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with file_path, "Parser returned null AST"
        proc deallocate from Layout with content
        Let _rfal2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal2 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with ast, 0

    If node_type is not equal to 200:
        proc print_test_failure with file_path, "Invalid root node type"
        proc deallocate from Layout with content
        Let _rfal3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal3 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    proc print_test_success from file_path
    proc deallocate from Layout with content
    Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Suite banner printed once at startup. Separator width (23 "=") matches
the title length so the heading visually aligns in CI logs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate title via StringCore, print via runtime primitive, deallocate;
same for the "=" rule. Always returns 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_header" returns Integer:
    Let header be proc create_string from StringCore with "CSS Parser Test Suite"
    proc print from header
    proc deallocate from Layout with header

    Let separator be proc create_string from StringCore with "======================="
    proc print from separator
    proc deallocate from Layout with separator

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits "[PASS] <path>" line. Splits from print_test_failure so grep on
"[FAIL]" cleanly isolates regressions in CI output. file_path doubles
as both the corpus identifier and the human label here because each
stylesheet name uniquely identifies the test.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[PASS] " prefix, print prefix, print caller-owned file_path,
deallocate the prefix. file_path is not freed (caller-owned).
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_success" takes file_path as Integer returns Integer:
    Let pass_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "[PASS] "
    proc print from pass_msg
    proc print from file_path
    proc deallocate from Layout with pass_msg

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits "[FAIL] <path>: <reason>" line. reason is one of "Failed to read
file", "Parser returned null AST", "Invalid root node type" so the
failure log shows the exact phase that broke (I/O vs lex/parse vs
structural tag check) without grepping upstream context.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[FAIL] " prefix, print prefix/file_path/": "/reason in order,
then deallocate the prefix. file_path and reason are caller-owned.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_failure" takes file_path as Integer, reason as Integer returns Integer:
    Let fail_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "[FAIL] "
    proc print from fail_msg
    proc print from file_path
    proc print with ": "
    proc print from reason
    proc deallocate from Layout with fail_msg

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Final summary block. Reads counters through type-checked struct field
access (results.total etc.) at the report site even though the hot
path in test_parse_file uses raw memory_get_int64 for uniform handle
semantics.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Print "=" rule, "Test Results:" heading, then Total/Passed/Failed lines.
Each label allocated/printed/deallocated; numbers go through print_int.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_results" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let separator be proc create_string from StringCore with "======================="
    proc print from separator
    proc deallocate from Layout with separator

    Let summary be proc create_string from StringCore with "Test Results:"
    proc print from summary
    proc deallocate from Layout with summary

    Let total_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "Total: "
    proc print from total_msg
    proc print_int with results.total
    proc deallocate from Layout with total_msg

    Let passed_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "Passed: "
    proc print from passed_msg
    proc print_int with results.passed
    proc deallocate from Layout with passed_msg

    Let failed_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "Failed: "
    proc print from failed_msg
    proc print_int with results.failed
    proc deallocate from Layout with failed_msg

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local integer formatter kept in each test file so the suite has no
dependency on stdlib formatting (which pulls in allocators not yet
bound at this layer of the bootstrap). Zero and negative values are
handled explicitly so single-digit and sign edge cases don't fall
through the divmod loop.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. value == 0 -> print "0", return.
2. Allocate 32-byte buffer; walk position 31 downward, writing
   48 + (temp % 10), dividing temp by 10 each pass.
3. For negative values: operate on -temp during the loop, then write
   '-' (45) at the final position.
4. Increment position once to land on the first written byte, print
   buffer+position as a C string, deallocate the buffer.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_int" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Let zero be proc create_string from StringCore with "0"
        proc print from zero
        proc deallocate from Layout with zero
        Return 1
    End If

    Let buffer be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    Let position be 31
    Let temp be value

    If temp is less than 0:
        Set temp to -temp
    End If

    While temp is greater than 0:
        Let digit be temp modulo by 10
        Let char be 48 plus digit
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position, char
        Set position to position minus 1
        Set temp to temp divided by 10
    End While

    If value is less than 0:
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position, 45
        Set position to position minus 1
    End If

    Set position to position plus 1
    Let str_ptr be buffer plus position
    proc print from str_ptr

    proc deallocate from Layout with buffer

    Return 1
End Process

Note: End of CSS Parser Test Suite
